## Public marketing & content

### `/` — Landing (index)
- **File**: `app/page.jsx` (server component)
- **Purpose**: Hero search, featured parks (yell, yose, grca, zion, glac, acad), Park of the Day, testimonials
- **API**: `GET /api/parks?all=true&nationalParksOnly=true` (ISR 24h)
- **CTAs**: Ask Trailie, Discover Parks, Browse All Parks, Interactive Map
- **SEO**: canonical root domain

### `/home` — Authenticated home
- **Protected** via proxy (requires `trailverse_auth_token`)
- **File**: `app/home/page.jsx`
- **Purpose**: Logged-in dashboard / daily feed entry (not in public nav for guests)

### `/about`, `/features`, `/faq`
- Static marketing pages; monthly sitemap priority ~0.5–0.7
- Footer links from every page

### `/testimonials`
- **File**: `app/testimonials/TestimonialsPageClient.jsx`
- Public submission form + list; API `POST /api/testimonials` (`optionalAuth`), admin approve/feature

### `/magazine`, `/newsletter`
- Magazine layout: `app/magazine/layout.js`
- Newsletter signup flows; email via subscribers API

### `/chatgpt` — ChatGPT App Directory
- **File**: `app/chatgpt/page.jsx` (server component, indexable)
- **Purpose**: Marketing for the **published ChatGPT app**; CTA opens Apps Directory (`NEXT_PUBLIC_CHATGPT_APP_URL` or default `chatgpt.com/apps/trailverse/...`)
- **Tools showcased**: plan_trip, get_park_details, compare_parks, search_parks, find_events, multi-turn planning
- **Backend**: Same 5 tools as `mcp-server/` (see `06-mcp-chatgpt-cloud.mdc`)

### `/mcp` — Claude MCP connector
- **File**: `app/mcp/page.jsx` (server component, indexable)
- **Purpose**: Install guide for **Claude** (Desktop / claude.ai custom connector)
- **Connector URL**: `https://trailverse-mcp.onrender.com/mcp`
- **Note**: The MCP server is also what powers the ChatGPT app; this page targets Claude users specifically

Full MCP/cloud architecture: **`06-mcp-chatgpt-cloud.mdc`**

### `/privacy`, `/terms`
- Legal; yearly changeFrequency in sitemap

### Static reports (public HTML in `public/reports/`)
- `/reports/when-to-go.html` — crowd calendar (redirect from `/reports/when-to-go`)
- `/reports/national-parks-2025.html` — data report
- Built/updated via `next-frontend/scripts/build-when-to-go-data.py`

